y distributed (pi0 should be high)\\n- **Mostly significant p-values**: Tests behavior with mostly small p-values (pi0 should be low)\\n- **Custom lambda values**: Tests `pi0BootstrapWithLambda` with user-specified lambda ranges\\n- **Deterministic behavior**: Validates that pi0 estimates are in valid range [0,1]\\n\\n### 2. Q-value Calculation with Projections (2 test cases)\\n- **ofPValuesBy**: Tests q-value calculation with custom projection (tuple extraction)\\n- **ofPValuesRobustBy**: Tests robust method with custom projection\\n- Validates that projection functions work correctly for structured data\\n\\n### 3. Edge Case and NaN Handling (5 test cases)\\n- **All NaN p-values**: Both `ofPValues` and `ofPValuesRobust` return NaN q-values\\n- **Mixed valid and NaN**: Validates correct handling of mixed input\\n- **Single p-value**: Tests minimum case scenario\\n- Ensures robust error handling and appropriate propagation of NaN values\\n\\n### 4. Mathematical Properties (5 test cases)\\n- **Monotonicity checks**: Q-values must be monotonic when sorted by p-values\\n- **pi0 boundary conditions**: Tests with pi0=1.0 (all nulls) and pi0=0.1 (few nulls)\\n- **Q-value vs P-value relationship**: Validates q-values \\u003e= p-values when appropriate\\n- **Valid range**: All q-values must be in [0, 1]\\n\\n## Test Coverage Results\\n\\n### Qvalues Module\\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\\n| **Line Coverage** | 0/134 (0.0%) | **132/134 (98.5%)** | **+132 lines (+98.5 pp)** |\\n\\n### Overall Project Coverage\\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\\n| **Points** | 14,004/37,731 (37.12%) | 14,207/37,837 (37.55%) | **+203 points (+0.43 pp)** |\\n| **Methods** | 3,739/10,540 (35.47%) | 3,787/10,556 (35.88%) | **+48 methods (+0.41 pp)** |\\n| **Classes** | 2,441/4,154 (58.76%) | 2,470/4,170 (59.23%) | **+29 classes (+0.47 pp)** |\\n| **Branches** | 4,402/32,115 (13.71%) | 4,490/32,169 (13.96%) | **+88 branches (+0.25 pp)** |\\n| **Total Tests** | 1,552 | **1,568** | **+16 tests** |\\n\\nAll 1,568 tests pass successfully.\\n\\n## Replicating the Test Coverage Measurements\\n\\n### Prerequisites\\n```bash\\n# Ensure .NET 6.0 SDK is installed\\ndotnet tool restore\\n```\\n\\n### Generate \\\"Before\\\" Coverage Baseline\\n```bash\\n# From main branch\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_before.xml \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\\n```\\n\\n### Generate \\\"After\\\" Coverage (with new tests)\\n```bash\\n# After applying this PR\\ngit checkout test-coverage/multipletesting-qvalues-1760712099\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\\n```\\n\\n### Run Only New MultipleTesting.Qvalues Tests\\n```bash\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --filter \\\"FullyQualifiedName~MultipleTesting.Qvalues.Additional\\\"\\n```\\n\\nExpected output: **16 new tests passing**\\n\\n### Analyze Coverage for Qvalues Module\\n```python\\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\\n\\ndef get_qvalues_coverage(filename):\\n    tree = ET.parse(filename)\\n    root = tree.getroot()\\n    for cls in root.findall('.//class'):\\n        name = cls.get('name', '')\\n        if 'MultipleTesting/Qvalues' in name or 'Qvalues' in name:\\n            lines = cls.findall('.//line')\\n            total = len(lines)\\n            covered = sum(1 for l in lines if int(l.get('hits', 0)) \\u003e 0)\\n            print(f\\\"{name}: {covered}/{total} lines ({covered/total*100:.1f}%)\\\")\\n\\nprint(\\\"BEFORE:\\\")\\nget_qvalues_coverage('codeCov_before.xml')\\nprint(\\\"\\\\nAFTER:\\\")\\nget_qvalues_coverage('codeCov_after.xml')\\n```\\n\\n## Testing Strategy\\n\\nThese tests were designed to:\\n- **Validate statistical correctness**: Ensure q-value calculations follow Storey's method\\n- **Test bootstrap stability**: Verify pi0 estimation is in valid range and stable\\n- **Cover projection functions**: Test both direct and projection-based APIs\\n- **Handle edge cases**: NaN values, single elements, all-NaN inputs\\n- **Verify mathematical properties**: Monotonicity, valid ranges, q-value â‰¥ p-value relationships\\n- **Test boundary conditions**: Extreme values of pi0 (0.1, 1.0)\\n\\n## Background on Q-values\\n\\nThe MultipleTesting.Qvalues module implements Storey's q-value method (JRSS-B 64: 479-498, 2002):\\n- **Q-value**: Minimum false discovery rate at which a test is called significant\\n- **Pi0 (Ï€â‚€)**: Proportion of true null hypotheses in the data\\n- **Bootstrap estimation**: Uses resampling to estimate pi0 across different lambda thresholds\\n- **Robust method**: More stable for small p-values when test count is low\\n- **NaN handling**: Gracefully handles missing or invalid p-values\\n\\n## Future Improvement Opportunities\\n\\nBased on coverage analysis, additional high-value testing areas include:\\n1. **Signal Processing** modules (0% coverage in many):\\n   - FFT operations (158 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - PeakDetection (142+ lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - Wavelet transforms\\n2. **Linear Algebra**:\\n   - EVD module (288 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - LAPACK/MKL services\\n3. **Distributions**:\\n   - Bandwidth selection (110 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - Various distributions with 0% coverage\\n4. **BigRational** module (198+ lines, 0% coverage)\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003eCommands and Searches Performed\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n### Bash Commands\\n```bash\\n# Coverage analysis\\npython3 /tmp/gh-aw/agent/analyze_fshar