 SS + Factor2 SS + Interaction SS + Error SS\\n\\n### 3. Helper Function Tests (3 test cases)\\n- **createAnovaVariationSource**: Tests record creation with all fields\\n- **createOneWayAnovaVariationSources**: Validates one-way result structure creation\\n- **createTwoWayAnovaVariationSources**: Validates two-way result structure creation\\n\\n## Test Coverage Results\\n\\n### Anova Module  \\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\\n| **Line Coverage** | 0/158 (0.0%) | 152/158 (96.0%) | **+152 lines (+96.0 pp)** |\\n\\n### Overall Project Coverage\\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\\n| **Points** | 13,805/37,630 (36.69%) | 14,003/37,731 (37.11%) | **+198 points (+0.42 pp)** |\\n| **Methods** | 3,715/10,527 (35.29%) | 3,739/10,540 (35.47%) | **+24 methods (+0.18 pp)** |\\n| **Classes** | 2,419/4,141 (58.42%) | 2,441/4,154 (58.76%) | **+22 classes (+0.34 pp)** |\\n| **Branches** | 4,363/32,102 (13.59%) | 4,401/32,115 (13.70%) | **+38 branches (+0.11 pp)** |\\n| **Total Tests** | 1,539 | **1,552** | **+13 tests** |\\n\\nAll 1,552 tests pass successfully.\\n\\n## Replicating the Test Coverage Measurements\\n\\n### Prerequisites\\n```bash\\n# Ensure .NET 6.0 SDK is installed\\ndotnet tool restore\\n```\\n\\n### Generate \\\"Before\\\" Coverage Baseline\\n```bash\\n# From main branch\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_before.xml \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\\n```\\n\\n### Generate \\\"After\\\" Coverage (with new tests)\\n```bash\\n# After applying this PR\\ngit checkout test-coverage/anova-module-1760710996\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\\n```\\n\\n### Run Only Anova Tests\\n```bash\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --filter \\\"FullyQualifiedName~Anova\\\"\\n```\\n\\nExpected output: **13 Anova tests passing**\\n\\n### Analyze Coverage\\n```python\\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\\n\\ndef get_anova_coverage(filename):\\n    tree = ET.parse(filename)\\n    root = tree.getroot()\\n    for cls in root.findall('.//class'):\\n        fname = cls.get('filename', '')\\n        if 'Testing/Anova.fs' in fname and '/Tests/' not in fname:\\n            line_rate = float(cls.get('line-rate', 0))\\n            lines = cls.findall('.//line')\\n            total = len(lines)\\n            covered = sum(1 for l in lines if int(l.get('hits', 0)) \\u003e 0)\\n            return covered, total, line_rate * 100\\n    return 0, 0, 0.0\\n\\nbefore = get_anova_coverage('codeCov_before.xml')\\nafter = get_anova_coverage('codeCov_after.xml')\\n\\nprint(f\\\"Before: {before[0]}/{before[1]} lines ({before[2]:.1f}%)\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"After:  {after[0]}/{after[1]} lines ({after[2]:.1f}%)\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Improvement: +{after[0] - before[0]} lines\\\")\\n```\\n\\n## Testing Strategy\\n\\nThese tests were designed to:\\n- **Validate mathematical correctness**: Ensure ANOVA calculations follow standard statistical formulas\\n- **Test different ANOVA models**: Cover Fixed, Mixed, and Random effects models for two-way ANOVA\\n- **Verify degrees of freedom**: Confirm proper calculation for between/within groups and interactions\\n- **Test sum of squares partitioning**: Validate that variance components sum correctly\\n- **Handle edge cases**: Test scenarios with minimal groups, very similar means, and various design sizes\\n- **Verify result structures**: Ensure all helper functions create properly formatted results\\n\\n## Background on ANOVA\\n\\nThe Anova module implements:\\n- **One-Way ANOVA**: Tests if means of 2+ groups are equal using F-distribution\\n- **Two-Way ANOVA**: Analyzes effects of two independent variables and their interaction\\n  - **Fixed Model**: Both factors have fixed levels chosen by experimenter\\n  - **Mixed Model**: One fixed factor, one random factor\\n  - **Random Model**: Both factors have random levels from populations\\n- **Variation Partitioning**: Decomposes total variance into components (between-groups, within-groups, interaction, error)\\n\\n## Future Improvement Opportunities\\n\\nBased on coverage analysis, additional high-value areas include:\\n1. **Signal Processing** modules (0% coverage in many):\\n   - FFT operations (158 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - PeakDetection (142+ lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - Wavelet transforms\\n2. **Statistical Tests**:\\n   - MultipleTesting (134 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - Additional post-hoc test coverage\\n3. **Linear Algebra**:\\n   - EVD module (288 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - MKL service implementations\\n4. **Distribution modules**:\\n   - Bandwidth selection (110 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - Various distributions with 0% coverage\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003eCommands and Searches Performed\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n### Bash Commands\\n```bash\\n# Coverage analysis\\npython3 /tmp/gh-aw-trial-FSarpStats-claude/agent/coverage_analysis.txt\\n\\n# Branch creation\\ngit checkout -b test-coverage/anova-module-1760710996\\n\\n# Build and test\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --filter \\\"FullyQualifiedName~Anova\\\"\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release\\n\\n# Coverage generation\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml /p:AltCoverForce=tr