* |\\n\\nAll 1,539 tests pass successfully.\\n\\n## Replicating the Test Coverage Measurements\\n\\n### Prerequisites\\n```bash\\n# Ensure .NET 6.0 SDK is installed\\ndotnet tool restore\\n```\\n\\n### Generate \\\"Before\\\" Coverage Baseline\\n```bash\\n# From main branch\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_before.xml \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\\n```\\n\\n### Generate \\\"After\\\" Coverage (with new tests)\\n```bash\\n# After applying this PR\\ngit checkout test-coverage/quantile-complete-1760710124\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\\n```\\n\\n### Run Only Quantile Tests\\n```bash\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --filter \\\"FullyQualifiedName~Quantile\\\"\\n```\\n\\nExpected output: **37 Quantile tests passing** (up from 19)\\n\\n## Testing Strategy\\n\\nThese tests were designed to:\\n- **Validate mathematical correctness**: Ensure all quantile methods produce expected results against R stats 3.6.2\\n- **Test all quantile types**: Cover Types 1-9 quantile estimation methods\\n- **Test edge cases**: Boundary conditions (q=0, q=1, negative values)\\n- **Verify in-place behavior**: Ensure InPlace methods work correctly with array modifications\\n- **Test utility functions**: Validate IQR and batch percentile calculations\\n\\n## Background on Quantile Methods\\n\\nThe Quantile module implements 9 different quantile estimation methods:\\n- **Type 1**: Inverse of empirical CDF\\n- **Type 2**: Averaging at discontinuities\\n- **Type 3**: SAS definitio