{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_01UQciw1qVZFkajnhWyb8KC2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ApzwfgPiGU1DhxZBvdyf8R","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/runner/work/gh-aw-trial-FSarpStats-claude/gh-aw-trial-FSarpStats-claude/tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Signal.fs","old_string":"            testCase \"finds optimal window for noisy signal\" <| fun() ->\n                // Create blank signal (noise only)\n                let rnd = System.Random(42)\n                let blankSignal = Array.init 100 (fun _ -> rnd.NextDouble() * 0.1 - 0.05)\n\n                // Create signal of interest (sine wave + noise)\n                let signalOfInterest =\n                    Array.init 100 (fun i ->\n                        let t = float i * 0.2\n                        sin(t) + rnd.NextDouble() * 0.1 - 0.05)\n\n                let windowsToTest = [|3; 5; 7; 9; 11|]\n                let optimalWindow = Signal.Filtering.optimizeWindowWidth 2 windowsToTest blankSignal signalOfInterest\n\n                // Should return one of the test windows\n                Expect.contains windowsToTest optimalWindow \"Should return one of the tested windows\"\n                // Should be an odd number\n                Expect.equal (optimalWindow % 2) 1 \"Optimal window should be odd\"\n\n            testCase \"filters out even window sizes\" <| fun() ->\n                let blankSignal = Array.init 50 (fun i -> float i * 0.01)\n                let signalOfInterest = Array.init 50 (fun i -> float i * 0.02)\n\n                // Include even numbers in test array\n                let windowsToTest = [|2; 3; 4; 5; 6; 7|]\n                let optimalWindow = Signal.Filtering.optimizeWindowWidth 2 windowsToTest blankSignal signalOfInterest\n\n                // Should only consider odd windows\n                Expect.isTrue (optimalWindow % 2 = 1) \"Should filter out even windows\"\n                Expect.contains [|3; 5; 7|] optimalWindow \"Should only pick from odd windows\"\n\n            testCase \"works with small dataset\" <| fun() ->\n                let blankSignal = [|0.1; 0.05; 0.15; 0.08; 0.12; 0.09; 0.11; 0.07; 0.13; 0.10|]\n                let signalOfInterest = [|1.0; 1.5; 1.2; 1.8; 1.6; 2.0; 1.9; 2.2; 2.1; 2.3|]\n\n                let windowsToTest = [|3; 5|]\n                let optimalWindow = Signal.Filtering.optimizeWindowWidth 2 windowsToTest blankSignal signalOfInterest\n\n                Expect.contains windowsToTest optimalWindow \"Should return valid window\"\n\n            testCase \"returns valid result for various polynomial orders\" <| fun() ->\n                let rnd = System.Random(123)\n                let blankSignal = Array.init 100 (fun _ -> rnd.NextDouble() * 0.2)\n                let signalOfInterest = Array.init 100 (fun i -> float i * 0.1 + rnd.NextDouble() * 0.2)\n\n                let windowsToTest = [|5; 7; 9; 11|]\n\n                // Test with different polynomial orders\n                for polOrder in [2; 3; 4] do\n                    let optimalWindow = Signal.Filtering.optimizeWindowWidth polOrder windowsToTest blankSignal signalOfInterest\n                    Expect.contains windowsToTest optimalWindow $\"Should work with polynomial order {polOrder}\"","new_string":"            testCase \"finds optimal window for noisy signal\" <| fun() ->\n                // Create blank signal (noise only)\n                let rnd = System.Random(42)\n                let blankSignal = Array.init 100 (fun _ -> rnd.NextDouble() * 0.1 - 0.05)\n\n                // Create signal of interest (sine wave + noise)\n                let signalOfInterest =\n                    Array.init 100 (fun i ->\n                        let t = float i * 0.2\n                        sin(t) + rnd.NextDouble() * 0.1 - 0.05)\n\n                // For order=2, windowSize must be > order+1, so minimum is 5\n                let windowsToTest = [|5; 7; 9; 11|]