{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_01JughHy9hceqLirecgofLom","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016nuUtXceuPT7pJu4g8XVFv","name":"mcp__safe_outputs__create_pull_request","input":{"title":"Daily Test Coverage Improver - Signal.Filtering Module Tests","body":"## Summary\n\nAdded comprehensive test coverage for the **Signal.Filtering** module, achieving **94% line coverage** and **77% branch coverage** for a previously untested signal processing module. This PR adds **18 new test cases** covering the Savitzky-Golay filter and window width optimization functionality.\n\n## Problems Found\n\nThe `Signal/Filtering` module had **0% test coverage** despite providing essential signal processing functionality:\n- Savitzky-Golay low-pass filter for smoothing noisy data\n- Derivative calculation capabilities (1st and 2nd derivatives)\n- Automatic window width optimization based on noise characteristics\n- Critical signal processing operations with no validation\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n### 1. Savitzky-Golay Basic Smoothing Tests (4 test cases)\n- **Noisy sine wave smoothing**: Tests smoothing with realistic noisy data\n- **Linear data preservation**: Validates polynomial fit preserves linear trends\n- **Quadratic data with order=2**: Tests polynomial order matching data complexity\n- **Output length validation**: Ensures output matches input length\n\n### 2. Derivative Calculation Tests (3 test cases)\n- **First derivative of linear function**: Tests d/dx(2x) = 2\n- **First derivative of quadratic**: Validates d/dx(xÂ²) = 2x at specific points\n- **Second derivative of quadratic**: Tests dÂ²/dxÂ²(xÂ²) = 2 (constant)\n\n### 3. Error Handling Tests (4 test cases)\n- **windowSize must be odd**: Validates rejection of even window sizes\n- **windowSize must be positive**: Tests zero and negative parameter rejection\n- **order must be >= derivative order**: Ensures polynomial order sufficiency\n- **windowSize vs polynomial order**: Validates windowSize > order + 1 requirement\n\n### 4. Edge Case Tests (3 test cases)\n- **Minimum valid configuration**: Tests smallest valid parameters (window=3, order=1)\n- **Single peak removal**: Validates outlier spike smoothing\n- **Constant signal handling**: Ensures constant data remains constant after filtering\n\n### 5. Window Width Optimization Tests (4 test cases)\n- **Optimal window for noisy signal**: Tests autocorrelation-based optimization\n- **Even window filtering**: Validates automatic filtering to odd windows only\n- **Small dataset handling**: Tests with minimal data (10 points)\n- **Various polynomial orders**: Tests orders 2, 3, and 4 with appropriate windows\n\n## Test Coverage Results\n\n### Filtering Module (Signal/Filtering.fs)\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\n| **Line Coverage** | 0/62 (0.0%) | **58/62 (94.0%)** | **+58 lines (+94.0 pp)** |\n| **Branch Coverage** | 0% | **77.0%** | **+77.0 pp** |\n\n### Overall Project Coverage\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\n| **Total Tests** | 1,612 | **1,630** | **+18 tests** |\n| **Line Coverage** | 38.23% | 38.53% | +0.30 pp |\n| **Methods Covered** | 3,896/10,652 | 3,936/10,679 | +40 methods |\n| **Classes Covered** | 2,565/4,265 | 2,595/4,291 | +30 classes |\n\nAll 1,630 tests pass successfully.\n\n## Replicating the Test Coverage Measurements\n\n### Prerequisites\n```bash\n# Ensure .NET 6.0 SDK is installed\ndotnet tool restore\n```\n\n### Generate \"Before\" Coverage Baseline\n```bash\n# From main branch\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --no-build \\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_before.xml \\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\n```\n\n### Generate \"After\" Coverage (with new tests)\n```bash\n# After applying this PR\ngit checkout test-coverage/signal-filtering-1760714661\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --no-build \\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml \\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\n```\n\n### Run Only New Filtering Tests\n```bash\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~FilteringTests\"\n```\n\nExpected output: **18 new tests passing**\n\n### Analyze Coverage for Filtering Module\n```python\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n\ndef get_filtering_coverage(filename):\n    tree = ET.parse(filename)\n    root = tree.getroot()\n    for cls in root.findall('.//class'):\n        fname = cls.get('filename', '')\n        if 'Signal/Filtering.fs' in fname and '/Tests/' not in fname:\n            lines = cls.findall('.//line')\n            total = len(lines)\n            covered = sum(1 for l in lines if int(l.get('hits', 0)) > 0)\n            line_rate = float(cls.get('line-rate', 0))\n            branch_rate = float(cls.get('branch-rate', 0))\n            return covered, total, line_rate * 100, branch_rate * 100\n    return 0, 0, 0.0, 0.0\n\nbefore = get_filtering_coverage('codeCov_before.xml')\nafter = get_filtering_coverage('codeCov_after.xml')\n\nprint(f\"BEFORE: {before[0]}/{before[1]} lines ({before[2]:.1f}% line, {before[3]:.1f}% branch)\")\nprint(f\"AFTER:  {after[0]}/{after[1]} lines ({after[2]:.1f}% line, {after[3]:.1f}% branch)\")\nprint(f\"IMPROVEMENT: +{after[0] - before[0]} lines (+{after[2] - before[2]:.1f} pp)\")\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\nThese tests were designed to:\n- **Validate algorithmic correctness**: Ensure Savitzky-Golay filter works correctly for various data types (linear, quadratic, noisy signals)\n- **Test derivative calculations**: Verify 1st and 2nd derivatives match analytical expectations\n- **Cover error paths**: Validate all parameter validation and error messages\n- **Test edge cases**: Minimum configurations, constant signals, outlier handling\n- **Verify optimization**: Test autocorrelation-based window width optimization with different polynomial orders\n- **Ensure numerical stability**: Check for NaN/Infinity in outputs with various inputs\n\n## Background on Savitzky-Golay Filtering\n\nThe Savitzky-Golay filter is a sophisticated digital filter that:\n- **Smooths data** by fitting successive windows of data with low-degree polynomials via least-squares\n- **Preserves features** better than moving averages (maintains peak shapes and widths)\n- **Calculates derivatives** as a byproduct of the polynomial fit\n- **Widely used** in spectroscopy, chromatography, and general signal processing\n\nThe `optimizeWindowWidth` function implements the method from Anal. Chem. 2006, 78, 5, 1515-1522, which:\n- Estimates noise autocorrelation from a blank signal\n- Tests multiple window widths to find optimal smoothing\n- Balances noise reduction with signal preservation\n\n## Future Improvement Opportunities\n\nBased on coverage analysis, additional high-value testing areas include:\n1. **Signal Processing** modules (0% coverage in many):\n   - FFT operations (160 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - PeakDetection (300 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - ContinuousWavelet (164 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - Padding (276 lines, 0% coverage)\n2. **Other Filtering Methods**:\n   - Commented-out Butterworth and Chebyshev filters (if implemented)\n3. **Linear Algebra**:\n   - EVD module (288 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - LinearAlgebraServiceMKL (406 lines, 0% coverage)\n4. **Distributions**:\n   - Bandwidth selection (124 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - KernelDensity (118 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - Various continuous distributions (Exponential, Uniform, StudentizedRange)\n\n<details>\n<summary>Commands and Searches Performed</summary>\n\n### Bash Commands\n```bash\n# Coverage analysis\ntail -100 coverage-steps.log\npython3 (analyze coverage XML for low-coverage modules)\npython3 (compare before/after coverage for Filtering module)\n\n# Branch creation\ngit checkout -b test-coverage/signal-filtering-1760714661\n\n# Source code inspection\ncat src/FSharp.Stats/Signal/Filtering.fs\ncat tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Signal.fs\n\n# Build and test\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~FilteringTests\"\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release\n\n# Coverage generation\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build \\\n  /p:AltCover=true /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml /p:AltCoverForce=true\n\n# Formatting\ndotnet fantomas tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Signal.fs\n\n# Git operations\ngit add tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Signal.fs\ngit commit -m \"Add comprehensive tests for Signal.Filtering module...\"\n```\n\n### Web Searches\nNone performed - relied on existing project structure, coverage reports, and signal processing knowledge.\n\n### Web Pages Fetched\nNone - all information gathered from local repository files and coverage reports.\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\nðŸ¤– Generated by Daily Test Coverage Improver Agent","branch":"test-coverage/signal-filtering-1760714661"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":334,"cache_read_input_tokens":131663,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":334,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7b338836-d59e-4880-ac0d-e697ed099275","uuid":"1feb577b-bcf0-477e-acce-f34a9c9514c1"}
